COMMENT: Do you have any additional comments or suggestions?
Take some action when this survey is concluded. /  / Clever to use individual's name when requesting completion of survey.

I've found the new on-campus wireless system to be mostly unreliable. It often has trouble connecting and my device gets kicked out after a short period of time. /  / I do find the IT support staff to be very friendly and personable which I appreciate. I've always had very positive interactions when being assisted.  /  / Thank you!
The Helpdesk staff should travel to the offices of busy people rather than expect them to wait for upwards of 45 minutes sometimes for laptop support.

Allow for different positions to be designated whether they need a laptop or desktop computer. Positions like admissions counselors or development officers should receive special designation because our jobs require us to travel. ITS should supply laptops and docking stations instead of a desktop computer for these positions in the same manner that laptops are supplied to faculty members.

Regarding the library, please do not get rid of the books! Some of us still like to hold a book in our hands when we read. /  / Regarding ITS, my experience has been a mixed bag - the staff who come to fix my computer are great - no problem there - but the ones at the desk tend to be sort of cold and independent. I also find it exclusive and down right absurd that staff are not allowed laptops instead of workstations. There is no logical reason for this except someone's need to say no to a group of people.
wifi strength needs much improvement. consistent trouble with VPN as well
ITS does a great job based on the amount of people they have to deal with on campus.  Thank You
This survey was very difficult to read and complete on phone.  Suggest using software and formats that are phone friendly in the future.

I am not a fan of the premise that functional areas "own" their own technology.  Upper level employees spend valuable time configuring and trouble shooting systems when their skill set is not technology.

IT should find a way to provide regular comprehensive updates to computers so that we do not have to put in a ticket for service and have to wait because it is a "non-priority".  Then when we do get an update it is done by someone who is not knowledgeable enough to make sure that your "problems" are corrected.  The whole system is very frustrating.
I would have preferred NOT to have included self-describing data.

Your survey does not reflect employees who are also students.  I am in the Master's in Public Administration program and have been using Blackboard as a student for the past two years.  I feel that IT makes presumptions on what the role of Academic Administrative Assistants on campus.  When Banner replaced Ingres on campus there was a information gap that has not been filled and it has been a frustrating experience.  (Banner + Argos)  We need information in order to do our jobs and need access to information that we have not had.
ITS staff is awesome - they are just so busy, I have to wait for a response sometimes. But that's not their fault.
The wifi is so horrible. It's so bad that my coworkers and I are not able to use internet in our classrooms. We also can not sent attachments in our email. This should not happen.
